CONFIRMED genuine skip (#3) — needs the removed `emccanon.CANON_ERROR` binding.

The remap uses a prolog (prolog=failingprolog ngc=notcalled — the prolog form IS
portable), but the prolog's specific subject is `emccanon.CANON_ERROR("%s is a
literal percent s")`: it raises a canon-level error whose message contains a
literal %s, checking that the canon error path does not mis-treat it as a printf
format. gomc removed the embedded Python interpreter and the emccanon binding, and
the C interp_ext interp_ctx API has no `canon_error` accessor — a C handler reports
errors via ctx->set_error() (a plain string), which is a different path than
CANON_ERROR.

The prolog-fails-and-conveys-error capability is covered by remap/fail/prolog
(interp_ext set_error, see DISPOSITION §2e). The emccanon.CANON_ERROR literal-%s
case has no C equivalent to re-express against. Genuine removal.
